{"parse":{"title":"tagger","pageid":56679,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈtæɡə(ɹ)/}}\n* {{audio|en|En-au-tagger.ogg|a=AU}}\n* {{rhymes|en|æɡə(ɹ)|s=2}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{ety|en|:af|tag|-er|text=+|tree=1}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# One who or that which [[tag]]s.\n## The player who tries to catch others in the game of tag.\n##* {{quote-text|en|year=1989|author=Francis Edward Abernethy|title=Texas Toys and Games|page=111\n|passage=The teacher then calls on each one of the tagged to identify his '''tagger'''. If a student cannot guess correctly, he must sit down.}}\n## A person who writes [[graffiti]] using a specific mark\n## {{lb|en|comptheory}} A [[program]] or [[algorithm]] that adds [[tag]]s for purposes of [[categorization]], e.g. grammatical information to words in a document, or genres to songs in a music collection.\n##* {{quote-journal|en|year=2018|author=Clarence Green; James Lambert|title=Advancing disciplinary literacy through English for academic purposes: Discipline-specific wordlists, collocations and word families for eight secondary subjects|journal=Journal of English for Academic Purposes|volume=35|doi=https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jeap.2018.07.004|page=109|text=To include part-of-speech (POS) information, the corpus was tagged using the CLAWS '''tagger'''.}}\n# A device for removing [[taglock]]s from [[sheep]].<ref>{{R:Knight AMD}}</ref>\n# That which is pointed like a tag.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1689|author=w:Charles Cotton|title=Burlesque\n|passage=hedgehogs' or porcupines' small '''taggers'''}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|price tagger|tagger-along}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|person who writes graffiti}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|tagueur|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{rfe|en|Variant of [[tadger]]?}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|slang}} The [[penis]].<!--in Esquire. London: The National Magazine Company Ltd, 1992-->\n\n===Etymology 3===\n{{rfe|en}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|in the plural}} [[sheet|Sheets]] of [[tin]] or other [[plate]] which run below the [[gauge]].<ref>{{R:Knight AMD}}</ref>\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aeggrt|garget}}\n\n{{C|en|Genitalia|People}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|fr|taguer}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:bor|en:tag}}\n{{bor+|fr|en|tag}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|taguer}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-tagger.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Lyokoï-tagger.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jérémy-Günther-Heinz Jähnick-tagger.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Somain>>)}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{fr-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|fr|graffiti}} to [[tag#Verb|tag]]\n# to [[tag]] {{gloss|label}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|tagger quelqu'un sur Facebook|tag someone on Facebook}}\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{fr-conj-auto|type=er|pron=taguer}}<!-- not a -ger verb; hence 'nous taggons' not 'nous taggeons' -->"}}